6:
Hello? Hope you don't mind that we
let ourselves in...
10:
What a mess... Are all alchemists
this much of a disaster?
14:
Ugh... Hey, any of you know what
time it is?
18: Uh, a little past lunch, I think?
23:
Another failure then. It was
supposed to stop working 4 hours
ago.
25:
I suppose it might be impossible to
effectively incorporate shade
elements into sleep medicine...
29:
Someone from the Float requested
that we check on you and your
research, Bryce. That's why we're
here.
33:
Hmm, in other words, you're putting
me under observation.
36:
You don't appear to be government
lap dogs though.
38:
As the outsourced help, we're
supposed to keep you from doing
anything dangerous.
42:
Well, you don't look like you're up to
anything naughty. Sorry if we end up
getting in your way...
46:
Not at all. Whether I have an
audience or not makes no
difference to me.
50:
Let's see... What was the proper
procedure for tending to guests
again?
54: Uh... What're you digging around for?
58:
Tea. I'm supposed to serve that to
guests, from what I recall. Give me a
moment to synthesize some...
64:
This is probably the first time I've
ever had tea out of a beaker...
68:
I'm no alchemy expert, but is this
guy actually doing legit research?
'Cause it sure doesn't look like it.
73:
Bryce, are you sure wrapping the
test tubes with tape is safe?
78:
Why is everyone so obsessed with
safety protocols? I swear...
81:
What basis do you have for your
concerns? Do you even understand
what I am handling in the first place?
85:
S-so long as there are no issues,
then... Excuse me for saying
anything.
89: Ah... No, I'm sorry for snapping.
94:
Is this an elemental shard? It is
colorless.
97:
That's because it is inert, waiting to
be activated once more.
100:
Wait... Don't tell me you're actually
interested in the subject?
104: I am. Could you teach me more?
112:
My schedule is packed today. I don't
have time to give you a full lesson.
115:
Strange though. You don't have the
looks of a specialist...
119:
What are these test tubes wrapped
in tape for?
122:
These are spark elements,
converted into liquid form to be
used in medicine.
123:
Normally, elemental shards are
processed into useable energy
through an extraction technique
127:
But that is something to save for
another time. I have business
outside, and if you're going to follow
me, then don't dally.
131:
So... Mind telling me why we're on
the roof?
136:
What do you mean, why? Isn't it
obvious?
139:
Whatever, you just stand there and
watch.
145:
Hehehe... Yes, this is perfect. The
numbers are stable. It's working! I've
concocted enough as well!
154:
Hm? Why the scared looks? Are my
brains seeping out of my head or
something?
160:
Answer him! Else we'll hafta slap
some sense into you!
162: All this over some anti-rust spray?
170:
Floats are comprised mostly of steel.
Naturally, rust is a problem best
avoided.
178:
Of course not. I am an alchemist of
the highest caliber.
182:
Again, Bryce? You're not getting
away with it this time!
188:
No way! They're shutting down your
research and kicking you out? But
where will you live?
191:
My problems are a bit more
pressing than losing a home. It
seems I've been exiled from this
Float entirely.
194:
It beggars belief, honestly. Shouldn't
everyone wish to preserve the
structures holding up their homes?
198:
You know... You should've told
someone what you were doing
before you scared the crap outta
everyone like that.
206:
Well, whatever the case, I can't
change the past. I'll just have to find
a new place to conduct research.
210:
If you need somewhere to stay, I
know just the place.
216:
Excuse me? What's the meaning of
this?
220:
She means that we can get you set
up with a roof over your head and a
place to do work.
225:
I understood that part, but why
extend such an invitation to me?
What are you after?
229: To provide you with what you need.
231:
Also, I wish to continue the lesson
from earlier.
240:
Driven only by a single motive... How
nostalgic.
243:
All right, I accept. You've garnered
my curiosity as well.
246: I look forward to working with you.
